    <rule>
        <name>AS_CO_UT_triggerRefresh</name>
        <uuid>_a-0000e3c8-6861-8000-9ba2-011c48011c48_124064</uuid>
        <description>This rule takes in a local variable called local!triggerRefresh and changes the value of it. This is used to refresh a!refreshVariable() in some scenarios.</description>
        <parentUuid>_a-0000e2ad-62e7-8000-9ba2-011c48011c48_73105</parentUuid>
        <visibility>
            <advertise>false</advertise>
            <hierarchy>true</hierarchy>
            <indexable>true</indexable>
            <quota>false</quota>
            <searchable>true</searchable>
            <system>false</system>
            <unlogged>false</unlogged>
        </visibility>
        <definition>/*

Use this rule in any saveInto to update the value of a local variable triggerRefresh.

It should be used in conjunction with a local variable configured to refresh
whenever this rule is executed. To configure the local variable you intend to refresh,
set it up like this:

a!localVariables(
  local!triggerRefresh: now(),

  local!data: a!refreshVariable(
    value: ..(value definition)..,
    refreshOnVarChange: local!triggerRefresh
  )
)

*/

a!save(
  ri!triggerRefresh,
  ri!triggerRefresh + 1
)</definition>
        <namedTypedValue>
            <name>triggerRefresh</name>
            <type>
                <name>dateTime</name>
                <namespace>http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema</namespace>
            </type>
        </namedTypedValue>
        <preferredEditor>legacy</preferredEditor>
        <offlineEnabled>false</offlineEnabled>
    </rule>
